                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>According to Ehrman, p. 517, Churchill, on the day of his arrival at Quebec,
                    spoke to Leahy about the participation of the British fleet in the Pacific war
                    and “was told that its offer had been accepted”. For further discussion of this
                    subject at the meeting of the Combined Chiefs of Staff with Roosevelt and
                    Churchill on September 13, 1944, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                        target="#pg_315">p. 315</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
